  <idinfo>
    <citation>
      <citeinfo>
        <origin>Greene, D.C., and Wolfe, W.J.</origin>
        <pubdate>1998</pubdate>
        <title>Superfund GIS - Aquifer Diffusivity in Tennessee.</title>
        <geoform>Series_Name  N/A
Issue_Identification  N/A
				</geoform>
        <pubinfo>
          <pubplace>Reston, Virginia</pubplace>
          <publish>U.S. Geological Survey</publish>
        </pubinfo>
        <onlink>https://water.usgs.gov/lookup/getspatial?diffus</onlink>
      </citeinfo>
    </citation>
    <descript>
      <abstract>This dataset represents aquifer diffusivity based on the streamflow-recession
index areas from Bingham (1986).
			</abstract>
      <purpose>To provide information on spatial patterns of ground-water residence time,
ground-water storage, and stream response to rainfall.  Applications might
include models of streamflow and ground-water (or contaminant) infiltration,
movement, and storage.
			</purpose>
      <supplinf>Procedures_Used:
The 1:500,000 scale mylar maps from Bingham (1986), were scanned into a 200 dpi
grayscale TIF image on a PC using a Contex FSS-3012t scanner.  The image was
then georeferenced in Arc/Info using the REGISTER and RECTIFY commands.  The
georeferenced images were used in ArcEdit as a backdrop for interactive on
screen digitizing.  The digitized linework was cleaned and built as a polygon
coverage.  The polygons were attributed with the recession index as reported
by Bingham (1986).  The coverage was then intersected with a 1:100,000-stream
coverage for Tennessee.  Stream mileage and square mileage area was attributed
to each polygon.  For each polygon, the following formulae were used to
calculate diffusivity:

DD = drainage density = stream_mileage / square_mileage
diffusivity = ( 0.933 * (DD / 2)^2 ) / recession_index

Revisions:
none

Reviews_Applied_to_Data:
none

Related_Spatial_and_Tabular_Data_Sets:
none

Other_References_Cited:
Bingham, R.H., 1986, Regionalization of winter-flow characteristics of
Tennessee streams: U.S. Geological Survey Water-Resources Investigations
Report 86-4007, 88 p.

Notes:
none
			</supplinf>
    </descript>
