    <overview>
      <eaover>The &lt;coverage&gt;.PAT data file contains four data fields.  POLY-REC-INDEX is
the streamflow-recession index for that polygon as reported by Bingham, 1986.
DRAINAGE-DENSITY is the miles of stream per square mile in that polygon.
DIFFUSIVITY is the aquifer diffusivity calculated for that polygon based on
the formula in the Procedures section of this document.  MILES-DRAINAGE is
the mileage of streams for that polygon.  SQ-MILE-AREA is the square mileage
contained in that polyon.
			</eaover>
      <eadetcit>Not Available</eadetcit>
    </overview>
